FAQs
What are the language requirements for studying medicine in Poland?

Many medical programs in Poland are taught in English, so proficiency in English is required. Some universities may also offer Polish language courses to help students integrate.

How much does it cost to study medicine in Poland?

Tuition fees for medical programs in Poland range from €7,000 to €15,000 per year. Living costs are generally affordable, averaging between €300 to €600 per month.

Can international students work while study in Poland?

Yes, international students are allowed to work part-time while studying in Poland. However, balancing work and study is crucial to maintaining academic performance.

What is the duration of medical programs in Poland?

Medical programs in Poland typically last six years, including both pre-clinical and clinical training.

Are medical degrees from Poland recognized internationally?

Yes, medical degrees from accredited Polish universities are recognized internationally, allowing graduates to pursue medical careers in various countries, subject to passing the required licensing exams.
